title: Ask HN: Is anyone else getting Twitter spam from Jack Butcher?
text:
Over the last 3 days I've received a ton of NFT-related Twitter spam.

It originally looked like they were using Jack Butcher's identity to promote a spam project (slightly misspelled profile name, etc). Then I checked out his real profile and it turns out its his NFT.

Anyone else receiving a ton of spam around this?

Ex: https://twitter.com/nizarbocahtrs/status/1621390195156287488 https://twitter.com/naochimu13/status/1621438241864908801 https://twitter.com/Anggundead/status/1621644083566354440 https://twitter.com/bloopbleepbop/status/1620786615269617666 https://twitter.com/unloved32/status/1621587013223825414

I'm trying to figure out what the scam is here or whether Jack Butcher is actually doing a bunch of sketchy stuff.
